2.25.66092044680927012484208907663249350.report_section_findings:
EXAMINATION: Single-view mammographic imaging of the left breast
utilizing standard mediolateral oblique projection.
FINDINGS:
The mammogram demonstrates heterogeneously dense fibroglandular
tissue distributed throughout the left breast. There is no definitive
presence of malignant-appearing masses or focal asymmetries. A few
benign-appearing cystic structures are noted in the upper outer
quadrant, characterized by round, well-circumscribed radiolucencies
without associated suspicious calcifications. Microcalcifications
present are predominantly coarse and scattered, consistent with
benign etiology. Skin and nipple contours appear intact without
retraction or distortion. No evidence of architectural distortion or
suspicious spiculations is observed. The axillary tail was partially
visualized with no abnormal lymphadenopathy discernible.
2.25.66092044680927012484208907663249350.report_section_impression:
IMPRESSION:
Findings are consistent with benign fibroglandular changes with
multiple simple cysts and no suspicious features warranting biopsy at
this time. Given the heterogeneously dense breast parenchyma, subtle
lesions may be obscured; correlation with clinical findings and
continued routine screening recommended. No interval imaging
available for direct comparison with this study. Recommend follow-up
mammogram in one year unless clinical changes arise.
Dictated by: Melissa Wright Interpreter, M.D.
2.25.66092044680927012484208907663249350.report_section_technician_note:
Patient mentioned slight tenderness during compression but tolerated
the procedure well overall. Advised gentle communication to minimize
discomfort in future scans.

2.25.20431047448279404156761903227368821.report_section_addendum:
ADDENDUM: Correction to the report: The initial assessment
underestimated the extent of the architectural distortion seen in the
lower outer quadrant. Additional magnification views and ultrasound
correlation are recommended for further evaluation.
2.25.20431047448279404156761903227368821.report_section_findings:
EXAMINATION: Single-view mammogram of the left breast.

FINDINGS:
The mammogram demonstrates heterogeneous breast parenchyma with
scattered areas of fibroglandular density. Notably, there is a focal
architectural distortion measuring approximately 1.2 cm located in
the lower outer quadrant of the left breast, without overt
calcifications. No discrete masses are identified within the imaging
field. The nipple-areolar complexes are symmetric, and skin contours
are unremarkable. No axillary lymphadenopathy is visualized on this
limited single-view study.
2.25.20431047448279404156761903227368821.report_section_impression:
IMPRESSION:
Heterogeneous breast density with a focal architectural distortion in
the lower outer quadrant of the left breast suspicious for an
underlying malignancy. Absence of discrete mass or
microcalcifications on the single view warrants further imaging with
targeted mammographic views and ultrasonography to characterize this
finding. Recommend tissue sampling if correlating sonographic
abnormality is found.
Dictated by: Erin Cervantes Interpreter, M.D.

2.25.29617871714165156649546618495566195.report_section_findings:
EXAMINATION: Lateral single-view X-ray imaging of the cervical spine.

FINDINGS:
The lateral cervical spine X-ray demonstrates progression of
multi-level degenerative spondylotic disease compared to the prior
exam dated 2025-08-14. Intervertebral disc space narrowing is now
more pronounced at both C5-C6 and C6-C7 levels. There is an increase
in osteophytic proliferation along the anterior vertebral margins
extending from C4 to C7, consistent with advancing spondylosis. The
vertebral alignment retains normal lordosis without evidence of
kyphotic deformity or acute subluxation. Facet joint hypertrophy
persists at multiple levels with worsening hypertrophic changes.
Neural foraminal narrowing at C5-C6 is more conspicuous bilaterally,
potentially increasing impingement on the exiting nerve roots. No
acute fractures or subluxations are detected. Prevertebral soft
tissues are unremarkable without signs of edema or swelling. The
odontoid process remains intact and well visualized.
2.25.29617871714165156649546618495566195.report_section_impression:
IMPRESSION:
Marked progression of cervical spondylosis compared to 2025-08-14,
with exacerbated degenerative disc disease at C5-C6 and C6-C7
manifested by intensified intervertebral disc space narrowing and
expanded anterior osteophytosis from C4 through C7. Facet joint
hypertrophy and bilateral foraminal stenosis have worsened,
increasing the risk of nerve root impingement which may correlate
clinically with exacerbated radiculopathy or cervical pain. Vertebral
alignment is preserved with no acute osseous injury or malalignment.
Continued clinical monitoring is advised, with consideration for
advanced imaging such as MRI to further evaluate neural element
involvement if symptoms progress.
